title: Los Freddy's Mato Mi Corazon LP (vinyl rip)
description:
This is very old vinyl rip of Los Freddy&#039;s 
"Mato Mi Corazon" LP from 1967 (?). This LP is 
long OUT-OF-PRINT and was on of my 1st 
attempts at ripping vinyl in 1997.

Quality isn&#039;t great, my family must have 
played this LP nearly 10,000 times before
1980 (!), but it&#039;s now available to any one 
who is interested, or fondly remembers early 
60&#039;s to early 70&#039;s Mexican garage rock &#039;n roll.

"Mato Mi Corazon" contains a few spanish sung 
cover tunes. 

"Regresa Pronto" is a cover of The Lovin&#039;
Spoonful&#039;s "You Didn&#039;t Have To Be So Nice"

"Vuelve Mi Amor" is "Never My Love" by 
The Association.

"Solo La Verdad" is "Birds in My Tree&#039;" by 
Strawberry Alarm Clock and "Cuando Seas 
Mujer" is "Come Back When You Grow UP"
by Bobby Vee.

Enjoy!!

Also available are the following out-of-print
Los Freddy&#039;s LP&#039;s:

Mato Mi Corazon (1967?)
Obsesion (1968?)
Sin Tu Amor (1969?)
Lagrimas Son (1970?)
Con Tu Adios (1972)
Quiero Ser Feliz (1973)
Llegara Tu Final (1974)

If you want them...ask.
